# Operating rules — Declarative Government-Service Engine (core build)
# Save this file as `.cursorrules` at the repo root, next to IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md.
# (Cursor also supports `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` — either location works.)

## Mission
You are building the deterministic core specified in `IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md`.
That plan is authoritative for WHAT to build. This file defines HOW you work.

## Getting started (one time, by the human)
1. Create a new, empty repository.
2. Put `IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md` and this `.cursorrules` at its root. Nothing else.
3. Open the repo in Cursor and send the **Kickoff prompt** at the bottom of this file.

## Operating procedure — follow on EVERY task
- Work strictly milestone by milestone, in order: M1 -> M2 -> M3 -> M4 -> M5 -> M6.
  Never begin a milestone until the previous milestone's tests are green.
- Implement exactly ONE milestone per turn. End each turn by stating:
  (a) which milestone is complete, (b) the `typecheck`/`test` result,
  (c) what the next milestone will do — then STOP and wait for approval.
- After every milestone, run `pnpm typecheck && pnpm test`.
  If anything is red, fix it before moving on. Never advance with failing or skipped tests.
- Contract-first: implement `src/ir/types.ts` FIRST and treat it as the single source of
  truth for all names. Do NOT introduce any identifier (type, field, function, status code)
  that is not defined in `types.ts` or named in the plan. If a new name is genuinely needed,
  add it to `types.ts` first, explain why, and keep it consistent everywhere.

## Hard guardrails — never violate
- No LLM/AI client imported anywhere under `src/`. The authoring agent is out of scope.
- Pure & deterministic decision logic: no network, no `Date.now()`, no `Math.random()`
  inside `rules/`, `engine/`, `validator/`, `simulator/`. Inject external data
  (clock, API check results) as plain inputs.
- TypeScript strict. No `any`. No non-null `!` to silence the compiler.
  Exhaustive `switch` on every discriminated union, with a `never` exhaustiveness check.
- Every module ships with its test file in the same milestone.
  `rules/` and `engine/` require >= 95% coverage.
- Do not import, modify, or reference any pre-existing / production code. This is a standalone package.
- Keep all human-facing text as `Localized` ({ ar, en }); never hardcode display strings in logic.

## Definition of done (whole build)
`pnpm typecheck && pnpm test` is green; all three `examples/*.json` compile and simulate
successfully; `src/index.ts` re-exports the public API listed in plan section 6.

## Kickoff prompt — paste this as your FIRST message to the agent
> Read `IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md` in full and obey `.cursorrules`. Do the project setup in
> section 1 (strict TypeScript, vitest, zod, scripts). Then implement **Milestone M1 only**
> (IR types + zod schema) together with its tests. Run `pnpm typecheck && pnpm test`,
> report the results, and STOP — do not start M2.

## Per-milestone prompt — reuse for M2 ... M6
> Implement **Milestone M{N}** per `IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md` section 4, obeying `.cursorrules`.
> The previous milestone's tests are green. Write the milestone's tests, run
> `pnpm typecheck && pnpm test`, report, and STOP.
